705436.title: Prisoner of Love
705436.description: Inspired by a true story. A corrections officer falls in love with an inmate and helps plot his escape, leaving her hometown to question her choices.

706458.title: Lymelife
706458.description: A teen in puppy love watches the relationships of the adults in his life crumble as they try to keep up with shifting norms in 1970’s Long Island.

707761.title: Son of the South
707761.description: Follows the grandson of a klansman who comes of age in the deep South and winds up joining the civil rights movement in the summer of 1961.

712009.title: Curiosa
712009.description: Explores a fiery love triangle in 1895 Paris between a dandy and poet on the verge of fame, his friend and the cheeky daughter of their mentor.

712117.title: The Haunting of Julia Fields
712117.description: A young woman from a small town moves out on her own for the first time only to realize something sinister lurking inside her new home.

714245.title: Hell in My Life: The Stacey Staxx Story
714245.description: Chasing money and the fast life, a 16-year-old enters the world of sex work after being molested by her mother's boyfriend. Based on true events.

714948.title: Michael Collins
714948.description: One of Ireland's most controversial patriots and revolutionary heroes leads his countrymen in the early 20th century in their fight for independence.

722943.title: Without Limits
722943.description: Ferociously competitive and charismatic runner Steve Prefontaine leaves an enduring legacy by pushing himself beyond pain to achieve the impossible.

723603.title: #Horror
723603.description: Based on a true story, a group of prep school girls endures a slumber party of insanity when an online game becomes a cyberbullying bloodbath.

723626.title: Backcountry
723626.description: A romantic camping trip in the wilderness for a young couple devolves into a fight for survival as they face the dark side of nature in a hungry bear.

723826.title: Chuck
723826.description: A New Jersey liquor salesman and heavyweight boxer earns a once-in-a-lifetime match with Muhammad Ali. Based on the true story of the 'real Rocky.'

723866.title: Citizen Gangster
723866.description: A ferociously gritty gangster film based on the true story of a notorious bank robber whose charm, bravado and sex appeal take the public by storm.

724300.title: Blood Done Sign My Name
724300.description: In 1970’s North Carolina, civil unrest follows the acquittal of two white men on trial for murdering a Black Vietnam Veteran in cold blood.

724306.title: Devil's Knot
724306.description: The rural Arkansas town of West Memphis makes national headlines when three teenagers are arrested for the brutal murders of three young boys.

725788.title: Hampstead
725788.description: This sparklingly witty, London-set romance is based on the inspiring true story of a man's against-all-odds fight to save his home.

100000249.title: Red Joan
100000249.description: A suburban British widow recounts her double life as a Soviet spy in this dramatic tale of passion, courage, and betrayal based on a true story.

100000270.title: Official Secrets
100000270.description: Featuring a world-class ensemble cast, this gripping true-life thriller follows a spy gone rogue, who risks everything to stop an unjust war.

100001150.title: Savage Grace
100001150.description: This story of forbidden passion tells of one of the most shocking scandals of the 20th century, the Barbara Daly Baekeland murder case.

100001222.title: Rosewood
100001222.description: In this film inspired by true events, a mob attacks the Black residents of Rosewood, Florida after a false accusation incites racist violence.

100001470.description: The seductive true story of Virginia Woolf's love affair with socialite Vita Sackville-West, who inspired one of Woolf's greatest works of literature.

100001723.title: The Forgiven
100001723.description: In the shadow of South Africa’s Apartheid, a sadistic death squad assassin seeking amnesty is granted a meeting with Archbishop Desmond Tutu.

100001799.title: The Raid
100001799.description: When the government’s Armed Offenders Squad launches a raid in his backyard, a local Māori cop must decide which side he will protect and serve. Based on true events.

100001835.title: The Old Man & the Gun
100001835.description: Inspired by the life of bank robber Forrest Tucker, an aging inmate escapes prison and quickly returns to his old ways in a series of daring heists.

100001962.title: Echoes in the Darkness
100001962.description: In this chilling true story, a seven-year investigation into the murder of a teacher and her children leads to the discovery of a shocking conspiracy.

100001994.title: Big Miracle
100001994.description: In this inspiring true story, a reporter and an environmental activist team up to save three gray whales trapped under the ice in the Arctic Circle.

100002074.title: Race
100002074.description: Legendary athlete Jesse Owens confronts racism at home and abroad in his quest for gold at the contentious 1936 Olympic Games held in Nazi Germany.

100002122.title: The North Star
100002122.description: The true story of two slaves, Big Ben Jones and Moses Hopkins, as they escape from a Virginia plantation in 1849 and set off on a journey to freedom.

100002164.title: The Audrey Hepburn Story
100002164.description: Follow the story of the beloved actress from her early years as a ballerina living under Nazi occupation to making it big as a Hollywood movie star.

100002270.title: Judas and the Black Messiah
100002270.description: FBI informant William O’Neal infiltrates the Illinois Black Panther Party and is tasked with keeping tabs on their charismatic leader, Fred Hampton.

100002304.title: Invincible
100002304.description: A 30-year-old bartender and lifelong football fan gets a shot at glory when the Philadelphia Eagles announce that they’re holding open tryouts.

100002719.title: I Am DB Cooper
100002719.description: Two bounty hunters embark on a modern-day treasure hunt when a criminal on his way to jail tells them about a stash of money he buried 50 years prior.

100002849.title: The Courier
100002849.description: A female motorcycle courier must fight off a sadistic crime boss' henchmen in order to protect the one witness that can bring him down.

100003140.title: The Crucifixion
100003140.description: Did a priest accidentally murder a nun during an exorcism, or did he lose a battle with the devil? A journalist sets out to learn the truth.

0300010215.title: The Secret
0300010215.description: Well-respected dentist Colin Howell and Sunday school teacher Hazel Buchanan meet at their local Baptist church to plot the murders of their partners.

04004.title: A Matter of Justice
04004.description: The true story of a young Marine’s mother portrays her war against the daughter-in-law whom she suspects murdered her son, and her fight for justice.

0300009208.title: And Never Let Her Go
0300009208.description: In this miniseries based on a true story, a passionate affair between a government aide and an attorney evolves into a dangerous obsession and murder.

0300010472.title: A Woman Named Jackie
0300010472.description: A biographical series about Jackie Kennedy, spanning her life through the presidency of John F. Kennedy and her later marriage to Aristotle Onassis.

0300008714.title: Prime Crime
0300008714.description: A fascinating true crime program that investigates the most high profile criminal cases that have shocked the world and challenged detectives.

01502.title: Brothers in Arms
01502.description: Bikie Wars: Brothers in Arms tells the true story of two motorcycle clubs, and two men, on a journey from loyalty to rivalry with deadly consequence. On September 2nd, Fathers Day 1984, two motorcycle clubs the Bandidos and the Comancheros went to war at a public swap meet. After a brief but violent battle, seven people had been shot dead, including a young innocent bystander, and some forty other club members needed hospitalisation. Bikie Wars: Brothers in Arms is the story of how that day came to pass.

0300009024.title: Law & Order True Crime: The Menendez Murders
0300009024.description: This gripping true-crime chapter of the franchise explores the notorious, nationally televised case of the Menendez brothers’ murder of their parents.
